### Example 1: Matches L1 backup appliance symptom (job failure)

**Input fields:**
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Short Description | Backup job failed for prod DB server |
| Description | Nightly full backup for production Oracle database server failed at 02:15. Checked the backup console and the job shows failed. Tried restarting the job but same error. The source server agent doesn't seem to be responding. |
| Error Code | *(empty)* |
| Work Notes | Checked bpcd service on source server - service is stopped. Port 13724 connection refused. No recent changes to backup policy or source server. Job was fine yesterday. |
| Configuration Item | NBU-APP-5240-PC01 |
| Category | Backup Operations |
| Product Name | Veritas NetBackup Appliance 5240 |
| Product Bar Code | SYS-VES-NBU5240-222 |
| Serial Number | NBU5240-SG-2024-0847 |

**Formatted search query:**
ISSUE: Scheduled backup job shows as failed for the production database server
SYMPTOMS: Job status shows failed in backup console, source server agent service stopped, port 13724 connection refused, manual job restart produces same failure
ERROR: Client agent not responding — connection refused on port 13724
SYSTEM: Veritas NetBackup Appliance 5240 (NBU-APP-5240-PC01)
CATEGORY: Backup Operations / Job Failure
DESCRIPTION: The nightly full backup job for the production Oracle database server failed at 02:15 with a client agent connection error. The NetBackup client agent (bpcd) on the source server is not responding on port 13724 and the service is confirmed stopped. The job had been completing successfully until last night with no recent changes to the backup policy or source server. Restarting the job manually produced the same failure.

